{
  "texts": [
    "We are also competitive with more complex domain matching approaches such as CBST, which involve the generation of pseudo-labels or the use of confidence-based selection strategies (Zou et al., 2019).",
    "However, compared to the results reported in Lv et al. (2021), our method falls behind DLMM, which achieves 70.47% accuracy, significantly better than our results.",
    "Nevertheless, a more detailed analysis reveals interesting insights when considering the improvements over the \"Source Only\" baseline.",
    "DLMM achieves an improvement of 6.83%, while our method has an improvement of 7.03%, which can be considered equivalent.",
    "That said, it is worth mentioning that our approach is characterized by its simplicity compared to DLMM."
  ]
}